==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hi-fi
<hw>hi-fi</hw></mhw> <ety>[shortening of
<ets>hi</ets>gh <ets>fi</ets>delity.]</ety> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An
electronic device that plays phonograph records, reproducing the
original sound with a high degree of fidelity. It superseded the older
phonographs, and itself is being displaced in popularity by CD
players.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hi-fi, high fidelity sound system.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

